[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#E74C3C]The Silent Problem Killing Your Player Engagement[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

You pushed 15 updates last month. Fixed critical bugs. Added requested features. Balanced the economy.

[B]How many of your players actually know about these changes?[/B]

Most server owners rely on chat announcements that get buried in seconds, Discord posts that only 30% of players see, or worse - nothing at all. The result? Players complain about "bugs" you fixed weeks ago. They don't notice new features. They assume the server is stagnant.

[B]You're working hard to improve your server, but your community doesn't see it.[/B]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#3498DB]ChangelogBook Changes Everything[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

ChangelogBook delivers your updates directly to players [B]in-game[/B], in a format they actually want to read - a beautifully formatted, interactive book GUI. No chat spam. No external links. Just clean, professional update communication that [B]players can't miss[/B].

This isn't another changelog plugin. This is [B]how premium networks communicate with their community.[/B]

[hr][/hr]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#2ECC71]What Makes ChangelogBook Essential[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[SIZE=4][B]Interactive Book GUI That Players Actually Read[/B][/SIZE]
Stop spamming chat with changelog messages that disappear in 3 seconds. Players open a beautifully formatted book with [B]sequentially numbered entries[/B], rich text formatting, and custom categories. It's intuitive, professional, and designed to be [B]read[/B], not ignored.

[SIZE=4][B]Smart Category System[/B][/SIZE]
Organize updates by [B]Added, Fixed, Removed[/B] - or create unlimited custom categories (Events, Security, Performance, Economy). Each category has custom colors, icons, and Discord embed styling. Your updates look [B]organized and professional[/B], not like random notes.

[SIZE=4][B]Reward System That Drives Engagement[/B][/SIZE]
Incentivize players to stay informed. Configure [B]customizable rewards[/B] for reading changelogs - items, economy bonuses, or permissions. Turn passive readers into [B]engaged community members[/B] who actually know what's happening on your server.

[SIZE=4][B]Automatic Join Notifications[/B][/SIZE]
Players get notified about new changelog entries the moment they join. No manual broadcasting. No hoping they check Discord. [B]100% visibility[/B] on every update you push.

[SIZE=4][B]Full Color Formatting Support[/B][/SIZE]
[LIST]
[*]Legacy color codes (&a, &c, &6) for all Minecraft versions
[*][B]Hex color support (&#FF5733)[/B] for Minecraft 1.16+ with automatic fallback
[*]Bold, italic, underline, strikethrough formatting
[*]Professional-looking entries that match your server's branding
[/LIST]

[SIZE=4][B]Discord Integration[/B][/SIZE]
Every changelog entry [B]automatically posts to Discord[/B] with rich embeds, category-based colors, author tags, and timestamps. Keep your Discord community and in-game players [B]perfectly synchronized[/B].

[SIZE=4][B]MySQL Database with Multi-Server Sync[/B][/SIZE]
Store changelog entries in MySQL for [B]network-wide synchronization[/B]. Update once, deploy everywhere. Includes HikariCP connection pooling, automatic database maintenance, and soft-delete with auto-prune. Built for [B]professional networks[/B], not hobby servers.

[SIZE=4][B]Multi-Language Support[/B][/SIZE]
Built-in English and Polish language files. Fully translatable for international communities. Every message, GUI element, and notification can be [B]localized to your audience[/B].

[SIZE=4][B]Admin-Friendly Management[/B][/SIZE]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Courier New]/changelog add [category] <content>[/FONT] - Instant entry creation
[*][FONT=Courier New]/changelog edit <id> <content>[/FONT] - Fix typos without recreating
[*][FONT=Courier New]/changelog delete <id>[/FONT] - Remove outdated entries
[*][FONT=Courier New]/changelog list[/FONT] - View all entries with IDs
[*][FONT=Courier New]/changelog reload[/FONT] - Hot reload without restart
[/LIST]

No complex setup. No YAML editing nightmares. Just [B]simple, powerful commands[/B] that work.

[hr][/hr]

